package com.infy; import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;
@SpringBootApplication public class 
DemoSpringBootApplication {
public static void main(String[] args) {
SpringApplication.run(DemoSpringBootApplication.class, args);
}
}
• @SpringBootApplication is a convenient annotation that adds the following:
o @Configuration marks the class as a source where bean definitions can be found for the 
application context.
o @EnableAutoConfiguration tells Spring Boot to start adding beans based on the class 
path and property settings.
o @ComponentScan tells Spring to look for other components, configurations, and, 
services in the packages being specified.
