JPQL Syntax
• Select clause: SELECT c FROM Customer c o SELECT c.customerName FROM Customer c
o SELECT c.customerName, c.dateOfBirth FROM Customer c
• Where clause: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.customerId = 1002; o Named parameter: 
SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.customerId = :customerId; o Positional Parameter: select c 
FROM Customer c WHERE c.customerId = ?1; o Equal: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE 
c.customerId = 1002 o Not Equal : SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.city != 'Seattle' o Greater 
Than: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.dateOfBirth > '1-Jan-1980' o Greater Than or Equal : 
SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.dateOfBirth >= '1-Jan1980' o Less Than: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.dateOfBirth < '1-Jan-1980' o
Less Than or Equal : SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.dateOfBirth <= '1-Jan-1980' o
Between: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.dateOfBirth BETWEEN '1-Jan-1975' AND 
'1-Jan-1980' o Like: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.name LIKE
'R%' o Is Null: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.emailId IS NULL o In: 
SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.city IN ('Seattle','Vancouver') o Is 
Empty: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.loans IS EMPTY o Is Not 
Empty: SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE c.loans IS NOT EMPTY o Suze: 
SELECT c FROM Customer c WHERE SIZE(c.loans) > 2
• Aggregate Functions:
o SELECT AVG(a.balance) FROM Account a o SELECT SUM(a.balance) 
FROM Account a o SELECT COUNT(a) FROM Account a o SELECT 
MIN(a.balance) FROM Account a o SELECT MAX(a.balance) FROM 
Account a
• String Functions 
JPQL provides string functions. These functions can be used WHERE and SELECT clause of query. The 
following table shows some of the string functions:
• Grouping and Ordering – The GROUP BY, HAVING and ORDER BY clause:
o SELECT c.city, COUNT(c) FROM Customer c GROUP BY c.city o SELECT 
c.city, COUNT(c) FROM Customer c GROUP BY c.city HAVING c.city IN 
('Seatle','Vancouver') o SELECT c FROM Customer 
c ORDER BY c.name ASC
• Update and Delete Queries:
o UPDATE Customer c SET c.city = 'Seatle' where c.customerId = 1002; o
DELETE FROM Account a WHERE a.status = 'INACTIVE'
